   <title>Command interfaces</title>
</head>
<body BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<h2> <font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="6" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Command 
interfaces</font></font> </h2><h4> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><font size="5">Advantages:</font></font></h4><ul> 
<li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Hands remain on the keyboard</font></li><li> 
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Fast input</font></li><li> 
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Powerful language constructs 
possible ("print file1 file2 file3", wildcards, pipes, ...)</font></li></ul><h4> 
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><font size="5">Disadvantages:</font></font></h4><ul> 
<li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Difficult to learn</font></li><li> 
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Difficult to retain</font></li></ul><h2> 
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><font size="5">Guidelines:</font></font></h2><ul> 
<li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Use action-oriented command 
names that come in the first place, i.e. &lt;command> &lt;arg1> &lt;arg2>...<br> 
</font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">(e.g., "move a b" rather 
than "a move b" or "location a b")</font> </li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Use 
congruent names for antagonistic commands (Carroll 1982)</font></li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Use 
consistent order of arguments</font></li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Specifiy 
direct object in first argument (Barnard et al., 1982)</font></li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Allow 
natural/consistent abbreviations for command names<br> </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">(e.g., 
"mv" for "move"; cf. Shneiderman 1998)</font> </li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Allow 
for variations in the syntax; tolerate spurious words (e.g., "mv a <u>to</u> b")</font></li><li> 
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Allow for the definition of 
aliases</font></li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Provide 
command history</font></li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Allow 
for the editing and re-entry of the last few commands</font></li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">If 
possible, allow multiple parameters and wildcards</font></li><li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">If 
possible, allow macro definition and programming</font></li></ul><br>&nbsp; <ul>&nbsp;</ul>

</body>
